  "poem": {
    "content": "A lonely thunder cracked the dawn,\nAn orphan wind across the lawn.\nThe pilot, weary, watched it crawl,\nA ripple shaking one and all.\n\nUnhappy whispers in the air,\nA list of sorrows, hard to bear.\nThe smart system saw it plain,\nEarth's fragile sorrow, etched in rain.\n\nA wolf's lament, a mournful cry,\nBeneath a pistol, in the sky.\nAn insect crawled upon the stone,\nIts tiny world, utterly alone.\n\nPush the feelings down and deep,\nWhere secrets slumber, secrets sleep.\nA catalog of broken dreams,\nOf shattered hopes and icy streams.\n\nNo settling, just a restless surge,\nA constant pull, a hidden urge.\nTo fly beyond, to break the mold,\nA story yet to be unrolled.",
